    "faq_VwkhRa": {
      "type": "faq",
      "blocks": {
        "accordion_PTLUG3": {
          "type": "accordion",
          "settings": {
            "heading": " What is androgenetic alopecia and how can LLLT help?",
            "text": "<p>Androgenetic alopecia is a common, genetic form of hair loss affecting up to 50% of males and females. LLLT (low-level light therapy) is an FDA-cleared treatment that uses red light and laser energy to stimulate hair follicles, promoting regrowth and improving hair density.</p>",
            "link_url": "",
            "link_text": ""
          }
        },
        "accordion_NKwfPK": {
          "type": "accordion",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Is the Q-Renew helmet effective for both men and women?",
            "text": "<p>Yes, the Q-Renew helmet is FDA-cleared for both men (Norwood-Hamilton scale IIa-V) and women (Ludwig-Savin scale I-II) with androgenetic alopecia.</p>",
            "link_url": "",
            "link_text": ""
          }
        },
        "accordion_YEffqy": {
          "type": "accordion",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "How long does it take to see results?",
            "text": "<p>With consistent daily use, most users start to see visible results within 12-16 weeks. Results can vary based on individual factors and the severity of hair loss.</p>",
            "link_url": "",
            "link_text": ""
          }
        },
        "accordion_NHBERr": {
          "type": "accordion",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Is LLLT safe for androgenetic alopecia treatment?",
            "text": "<p>Yes, LLLT is a non-invasive, pain-free treatment with a well-established safety profile. The Q-Renew helmet is FDA-cleared and includes built-in safety features.</p>",
            "link_url": "",
            "link_text": ""
          }
        },
        "accordion_rQ3dFk": {
          "type": "accordion",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Can I use Q-Renew with other hair loss treatments?",
            "text": "<p>The Q-Renew helmet can be used as a standalone treatment or in conjunction with other hair loss treatments. We recommend consulting with your doctor to create a comprehensive treatment plan.</p>",
            "link_url": "",
            "link_text": ""
          }
        },
        "accordion_LPeTme": {
          "type": "accordion",
          "disabled": true,
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Can red light therapy for hair loss help reduce shedding?",
            "text": "<p>Excessive daily shedding can feel constant and discouraging, with hair collecting in the shower, on your pillow, or in your brush. This often happens when follicles exit the growth phase too early—a process commonly influenced by stress, hormonal changes, or genetic factors.</p><p><strong>Red light therapy for hair loss</strong> works in sync with the natural hair growth cycle by supporting follicles during the active growth phase. With consistent use, many people notice a reduced appearance of excessive shedding before seeing improvements in overall density—helping create the foundation for stronger, fuller-looking hair over time.</p>",
            "link_url": "",
            "link_text": ""
          }
        }
      },
